<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PaLTM4.5.10">
<l>cettup pōvatōr pōtuni ṉaintu</l>
<l rend="indent">ceyyuñ ceykaikaḷ tēvapi rāṉmēl</l>
<l>patta rāyiṟan tārpeṟum pēṟṟaip</l>
<l rend="indent">pāḻit tōḷviṭṭu cittaṉput tūrkkōṉ</l>
<l>cittan naṉkoruṅ kittiru mālaic</l>
<l rend="indent">ceyta mālaiyi vaipattum vallār</l>
<l>cittan naṉkoruṅ kittiru mālmēl</l>
<l rend="indent">ceṉṟa cintai peṟuvar tāmē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Those who master this garland of ten composed about Tirumāl,</l>
<l rend="indent">by the king of Puttūr, strong armed Viṭṭucittaṉ,</l>
<l rend="indent">having concentrated [his] mind well,</l>
<l>about the blessing attained by those who die as devotees to the Lord of gods,</l>
<l rend="indent">and the deeds of those who think of [Him] at the time of death –</l>
<l>they are those who, having concentrated [their] minds well,</l>
<l rend="indent">obtain thoughts that dwell on Tirumāl.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
